JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 106
IS  - 2
SP  - 327
EP  - 368
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The Penn World Table displays a set of national accounts economic time series covering many countries. Its expenditure entries are denominated in a common set of prices in a common currency so that real quantity comparisons can be made, both between countries and over time. It also provides information about relative prices within and between countries, as well as demographic data and capital stock estimates. This updated, revised, and expanded Mark 5 version of the table includes more countries, years, and variables of interest to economic researchers. The Table is available on personal computer diskettes and through BITNET.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937941
ER  - 



