TY  - JOUR
AU  - Stokey, Nancy L.
T1  - Human Capital, Product Quality, and Growth*
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937948
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 106
IS  - 2
SP  - 587
EP  - 616
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A model of growth is developed in which finite-lived individuals invest in human capital, investments have a positive external effect on the human capital of later cohorts, and labor with more human capital produces higher-quality goods. Stationary growth paths are analyzed, paths along which human capital and the quality of goods grow at a common, constant rate. It is also shown that if a small open economy is either very advanced or very backward relative to the rest of the world, then its rate of investment in human capital is lower under free trade than under autarky.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937948
ER  - 



